  id: Deep_cervicoauricular_muscle.R
  partName: Deep cervicoauricular muscle Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right deep cervicoauricular muscle is a small muscular structure positioned
    between the deeper cervical tissues and the auricular region of the canine head.
    Its primary function involves assisting with ear movement, stabilization, and
    orientation during sensory and behavioral responses.
  - This muscle enables fine adjustments of the auricle, helping dogs localize sounds
    and communicate through changes in ear posture. It operates in coordination with
    surrounding auricular muscles to maintain smooth and responsive ear motion. Despite
    its modest size, the muscle contributes significantly to auditory awareness and
    expression.
